--EmDebug--

Description
===========

EmDebug is a front-end interface for GDB + OpenOCD, designed for debug ARM
Cortex-M based microcontrollers, allowing some advanced debug techniques like
showing information about the current exception, pending exceptions, HardFault
MemFault / BusFault / UsageFault information, peripheral's status, stack usage,
GPIO view and much more!


How to build
============

Pre-requisites:

- cmake
- libwxgtk3.0-dev
- g++
- make

Instructions:

Make a build directory then use cmake to generate the makefile:

emdebug$ mkdir build
emdebug$ cd build
build$ cmake ..
build$ make